@node pbmtolj



     pbmtolj(1)           AMIGA (29 August 1988)            pbmtolj(1)



     NAME
          pbmtolj - convert a portable bitmap into HP LaserJet format

     SYNOPSIS
          pbmtolj [-resolution N] [-float] [-noreset] [pbmfile]

     DESCRIPTION
          Reads a portable bitmap as input.  Produces HP LaserJet data
          as output.

          Note that there is no ljtopbm tool.

     OPTIONS
          -resolution
               Specifies the resolution of the output device, in dpi.
               Typical values are 75, 100, 150, 300.  The default is
               75.

          -float
               Suppresses positioning information.  The default is to
               write the sequence ESC & l 0 E to the output file.

          -noreset
               Prevents pbmtolj from writing the reset sequences to
               the beginning and end of the output file.

          All flags can be abbreviated to their shortest unique
          prefix.

     SEE ALSO
          @{"pbm" link pbm}(5)

     AUTHOR
          Copyright (C) 1988 by Jef Poskanzer and Michael Haberler.
          -float and -noreset options added by Wim Lewis.




















